<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="353" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,582,1723]" pageId="6" pageNumber="353">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,1662,1687]" pageId="6" pageNumber="353">Etymology</emphasis>
. The specific name is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[880,947,1662,1686]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="353">longi-</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[1011,1084,1663,1686]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="353">ovatus</emphasis>
, referring to the shape of the gnathos in the male genitalia.
</paragraph>
